cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DS

This paper deals with the problem of exploiting heap-based memory corruption vulnerabilities, which is a common issue in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a framework for benchmarking heap layout manipulation algorithms, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper discusses the implementation of a system called SHRIKE, which involves manipulating the PHP interpreter, making it relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses a search algorithm to achieve its goals, which is related to data structures (cs.DS).
